The goal of this study is to develop a smart phone/tablet app to administer a behavior change program that helps adults to increase daily steps by planning where, when, and with whom to walk.

 The investigators will test the effectiveness of various components of the walking program app for increasing the number of daily steps among sedentary older adults.

 The investigators also will examine the effects on self-efficacy and social integration/support.

